title: Trip of the week: England Coast to Coast Guided Walk
text:
Sunday August 2, 2015 5:00 AM 
Each week, Travel Editor Cindy Decker highlights an interesting travel package sent to her inbox. 
England Coast to Coast Guided Walk 
SHERPA EXPEDITIONS, 44(0)20-8577-2717, www.sherpaexpeditions.com 
THE TRIP: This 18-day walk offers the quintessential English hill-walking and long-distance-trail experience. 
The 190-mile expedition will start at St. Bees on the Irish Sea before heading east into the Lake District. The journey will continue into the Yorkshire Dales, along the River Swale and finally to the North Sea coast and Robin Hoodâ€™s Bay. 
The hiking is moderate to challenging. The package includes accommodations at cozy hotels, guesthouses and pubs; breakfasts; daily luggage transfer; guide; and return taxi service. 
THE COST: from about $2,250 per person, double occupancy
